    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Good morning, everyone! You are so good to me. I hope this first week of 2009 is off to a good start for you.</></>I just wanted to add one more thing that I forgot to mention in the recipe: Judith Jones&#8217;s remoulade is somewhat unconventional, in that it uses a bit of plain yogurt.  That&#8217;s part of what drew me to it, the thought of that yogurty tang.  And sure enough, it&#8217;s a wonderful addition: just a little tanginess to wake up and lighten up the mayonnaise and the mustard.  I think it&#8217;s a crucial part of what makes this particular recipe such a keeper.</p>
    </div>

