    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>The Tenth Muse sounds fascinating.  I&#8217;m thinking about getting &#8220;Hometown Appetites&#8221; by Kelly Alexander and Cynthia Harris.  I heard about it on NPR over the Christmas holidays and it is about one of America&#8217;s first food riders &#8211; Clementine Paddleford.  She worked for the New York Herald Tribune from 1936 to 1966 and contributed widely to other publications.  She traveled all over America learning and explaining how we eat.  Her book published in 1960 &#8220;How America Eats&#8221; is one of the most requested Out of Print books even after all these years.  She seems to me to be an interesting character and well worth learning more about.  I&#8217;ll write about it on SeattleRainydaybookblog.</p>
    </div>

